- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses non-classical atoms that can be used in knowledge representation and reasoning.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper introduces a variant of the Ehrenfeucht-Fra\""{i}ss\'{e} game, which is a well-known algorithmic tool in computer science.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possibility as the paper presents lower and upper bounds on the succinctness of various atoms in propositional team logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the expressiveness of a logical language.
